bib.title: Nuclear reactions of medium and heavy target nucleiwith high-energy projectiles. Fragmentation of Ag-natand Au-197 by 3.65 A*GeV C-12-ions and 3.65 GeVprotons.

free_txt: Lower Case. Elem/Mass Formalism was
Transformed to Usual Records.
Value of incident energy was changed
MeV to GeV, according B.Kiraly comment.
.The uncertainty is reported by authors.
.The errors assigned to the cross section
are based on those of counting statistics, detector
efficiencies and target thicknesses, a systematic error
of about 15% corresponding to the beam flux monitor is
not included.

For C-12 Beam
The target foils were enclosed in mylar catchers
17.5 mg/cm**2 thick.The induced Na-24 activity in the
Al-foil of thickness 20 mg/cm**2, surrounded by guard
foils of the same Thicknesses, was used to calculated
beam flux.
